pageProduct.name: Swisse Kids Multi 60 Tablets
pageProduct.description:
General Information

Swisse Kids Multi is a premium quality formula specially tailored for children. With 22 important vitamins, minerals and herbs including vitamins C & D, zinc and iodine.

? Vitamin C and zinc to help support immune function
? Iodine to help support cognitive development
? Vitamin D to support healthy, strong bones and teeth, as well as muscle health
? Great tasting
? Natural strawberry flavour
?99.9% sugar free
?Convenient chewable tablet
?No added artificial colours
?Ideal for fussy eaters

Size: 60 Pack

Warnings

Vitamin supplements should not replace a balanced diet. If symptoms persist consult your healthcare practitioner.

Ingredients

EACH CHEWABLE TABLET CONTAINS:
Betacarotene 500 mcg; Biotin 7.5 mcg; Vitamin B1 (thiamine from thiamine nitrate 228 mcg) 185 mcg; Vitamin B2 (riboflavin) 210 mcg; Nicotinamide 2.40 mg; Vitamin B5 (pantothenic acid from calcium pantothenate 1.18 mg) 1.09 mg; Vitamin B6 (pyridoxine from pyridoxine hydrochloride 255 mcg) 210 mcg; Folic acid 50 mcg; Vitamin B12 (cyanocobalamin) 0.4 mcg; Vitamin C (ascorbic acid) 35 mg; Vitamin D3 (colecalciferol 5 mcg) 200 IU; Vitamin E (d-alpha tocopheryl acid succinate 2.58 mg) 3.12 IU; Calcium (from calcium citrate tetrahydrate 238.10 mg) 50 mg; Iodine (from potassium iodide 65 mcg) 50 mcg; Iron (from ferrous fumarate 7.84 mg) 2.50 mg; Magnesium (from magnesium phosphate pentahydrate 48.40 mg) 10 mg; Manganese (from manganese sulfate monohydrate 5.91 mg) 1.92 mg; Zinc (from zinc sulfate monohydrate 5.51 mg) 2 mg; Citrus bioflavonoids extract 10 mg; Elderberry (Sambucus nigra extract 290 mcg) equiv. fresh fruit juice 10 mg; Nettle (Urtica dioica extract 2 mg) equiv. dry leaf 10 mg; Rosehips (Rosa canina extract 1.67 mg) equiv. dry fruit 10 mg.

Directions

2-8 years: Chew one tablet daily during or immediately after a meal.
9-12 years: Chew two tablets daily during or immediately after a meal.
Or as directed by a healthcare professional. Do not swallow whole.

STORAGE INSTRUCTIONS

Store below 25°C in a cool, dry place. Do not use if cap seal is broken.
